The chicken sandwich is made from the boneless breast of chicken seasoned with a spicy blend of peppers and a few other ingredients. Ingredients Toppings Preparation Step 1 Put the chicken and 1 tablespoon of oil in a sealable bag. Pound the chicken using a mallet to an even Â½ inch thickness. Step 2 Put in a small bowl, garlic powder, paprika, onion and cayenne. Step 3 Season the chicken with salt and the spice blend and garlic paste. Put in the bag and marinate for 20 minutes at room temperature. Step 4 Grill the chicken for 3-4 minutes on each side or until it reaches an internal temperature of 75 degrees. Step 5 Toast the buns and layer the lettuce, tomatoes, mayo and chicken on the bun. Add cheese and serve. Enjoy with a mock tail or cold beverage.